For Linux:

This requires boost libraries and UHD to be installed

For Windows:

Compile boost:

    Download sources
    Extract them in a folder, in my case C:\boost_1_55_0
    cd to that folder
    bootstrap.bat mingw
    b2 toolset=gcc

The way to compile it is: (I have C:\MinGW\msys\1.0\bin and C:\MinGW\bin in my PATH)

	Make sure you have Python/Cheetah/etc all of the prerequisites for UHD (look it up online)
	change uhd/host/lib/transport/CMakeLists.txt from IF(WIN32) to IF(MSVC) everywhere
	download libusb from http://libusb-winusb-wip.googlecode.com/files/libusb_2011.07.20.7z and extract into C:/libusb, so that C:/libusb contains libusb-1.0.lib, libusb-1.0.dll and libusb-1.0.dll.a and libusb-1.0/libusb.h for MinGW
	add the following lines to uhd/host/lib/usrp/b200/b200_iface.cpp
		#ifndef HAVE_LIBUSB_ERROR_NAME
			#define libusb_error_name(code) \
			str(boost::format("LIBUSB_ERROR_CODE %d") % code)
		#endif
	uhd\host\build>cmake -G "MinGW Makefiles" -DLIBUSB_LIBRARIES:STRING=C:/libusb/libusb-1.0.lib -DLIBUSB_INCLUDE_DIRS:STRING=C:\libusb\libusb-1.0 -DBOOST_ROOT:STRING=C:/boost_1_55_0 ../
	mingw32-make
	
